title: Fstop Labs 2 Pack Wall Ceiling Cabinet Mount Holder Stand Clip for Google Nest Home Mini Gen 1, Gen 2, Round Speaker Accessories (White) 2 Pack
top_review: Highly recommend this mount!Although relatively easy to install, I have really flimsy apartment walls that don't really grab on to nails and screws too well. I gave it 4 stars for "easy to install" because I had to remove the hardware and screw the screws into the little pegs all the way tightly to secure them to the mount before using a hammer to finish the job. It took all of less than 5 minutes. After that, it won't budge and very sturdily grips my mini. I'd suggest to plug it in after bringing the cord through the little hole at the bottom of the mount before clipping it into position.Overall, this mount is the most solid of the 3 or 4 I've owned thus far. My mini kind of just "floats" on the wall and the mount is pretty much invisible with just the cord hanging down.The device is responding much better to voice commands now that it's not muffled on my desk or knocked over by my curious cat!child. (Or at least she hasn't jumped at it yet. She's kinda more interested in the boxes from having recently moved!)This mount has also made the speaker sound quality a whole lot better and it actually fills my entire apartment at even 60% volume. Since the clip rests behind the fabric part, access to the physical controls/buttons is very easy and touching it for volume is completely unhindered. The mount stays perfectly out of the way while still securing the device to the wall.As with any wall mount where the power cord is on the bottom, make sure to flip the LEDs & volume controls in the Google Home app or your flashy lights will be backwards. Just go into the device settings and the option is near the bottom under "Reverse device controls".A very affordable little solution that's just exactly what I was looking for!

title: Wii U Gamepad Silicone Jacket - Black
availability: Only 1 left in stock - order soon.
top_review: The GamePad is the distinguishing feature of Nintendo's Wii U.  It will also be relatively expensive to replace.  (At the time of this writing, it is not even sold separate of the Wii U console, itself.)  It behooves one to afford it a reasonable amount of protection.  This silicone skin from PDP fits the bill, perfectly.The skin fits quite snugly over the GamePad and once on, does not feel flimsy or move about on the device.  It is not something I would want to remove and reapply on a regular basis, but thanks to PDP's thoughtful design, you don't have to:  this skin leaves exposed the portion of the GamePad that contacts the charging cradle, allowing the skin to remain on at all times (even when docked.)The material is not your typical silicone formula.  It has a much smoother feel, and does not attract lint like typical silicone.  Once applied to the GamePad, it has a feel of almost rubberized plastic or matte TPU material.  That is to say that it has a feeling of quality.  While the top portion is smooth to the touch, the underside has a slightly dimpled texture that aids in the gripping of the device; the texture is not unlike that of an orange peel.The buttons are all exposed and perfectly aligned, and while the skin does cause them to be recessed slightly, I find that it does not hinder their functionality whatsoever.Something not depicted in the product photos is the Wii U logo and the NFC marker (the rounded rectangle) which are painted in white on the skin in the same places as on the GamePad, itself.  As these are design elements of the actual GamePad, it is a tasteful addition to the product.  (To PDP's credit, they did not attempt to include their own logo or branding on the skin.)I am impressed by PDP's offering, and I can say that this is the most ideal skin/cover for the Wii U GamePad that I have encountered (and I have tried several.)  I can say that I highly recommend this product; if you are seeking protection for your GamePad, look no further.
